Dialogs.Dialog: Practice has been hard lately...
高嶺
Hehe, you look sleepy.
▲高嶺＊＊▲ is very energetic...
Maybe because I'm more experienced. I started playing tennis much earlier than you.
That's true, but...
Hey, could it be that you lack physical strength...？
Ah... That could be the case.
How about you try jogging every day？
I'd prefer to have some more sleep...
...Hmm, so you just want to sleep. Now, I can't think of other options.
(What shall I do...？)
高嶺
▲主人公＊▲. Why don't you find a part-time job？
？ What is it all of a sudden？
We were talking about training, right？ I talked with a classmate about it and he said part-time jobs helped him build stamina.
What kind of part-time jobs？
Carrying raw materials at construction sites. Also, working as a delivery man.
T-That's...
Impossible for you？
I guess...
I see... Maybe training regularly would be the best option, huh？
(Yeah, I'll do that！)
高嶺
I'm buying a new racket.
Why？
I've been using this one for a long time... It's getting worn out...
I see. ...Are you a bit sad？
Yeah... I really love it, so it's sad to have to buy a replacement...
Ah... But it doesn't mean that you have to throw it away once you get a new one, right？
Yeah.
Then you don't have to feel sad about it.
Plus, you may be able to find a new one that you really like.
...Um, that might be so. Hey, will you help me shop for one？
Ah, okay. Just tell me when you want to go.
Well, have you decided？
高嶺
I think I'll buy a replacement.
Ah, for your favorite racket？
Yeah, I found a new one that I feel comfortable with. Thanks for giving me advice.
You're welcome. What will you do with your old racket then？
I'll put it in my memory box.
Your memory box？ What is in there？
I've been putting a lot of things in there since I was in grade school. A mat that I made, some stickers that I collected...
But, maybe I should just leave the racket outside. It's pretty heavy, so it's suitable for swinging practice.
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ really takes good care of her stuff...)
高嶺
I wonder if it's hard to maintain good grades while attending club activities.
Why？
A classmate of mine who's in a different club said that.
When she gets tired from club activities, she feels too exhausted to study.
Ah, that's true.
Hey, do you think I don't practice enough？
Hah？
Because I've never felt exhausted to the point that I couldn't study. Does that mean I don't practice enough？
Maybe I should ask the captain for personalized, intensive training...
(I think you already practice very hard... You're amazing, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
How's everything going after you increased your practice？
高嶺
Well, it was more tiring, but not to the point that I fell asleep once I got home. I should extend my practice time...
No, no, no. Don't do that.
Eh？ Why？
You'll hurt yourself if you practice too much！
...Okay, but...
Most importantly, you'll have less time to spend with me！
If you say so, I...
...Okay. I'll just practice regularly.
(...Phew.)
高嶺
Hey, have you heard？ Our club is going to change its uniform？
Yeah, I've heard they hired a famous designer this time. I wonder if it's true.
Really？ That would be nice.
Hmm？ Are you interested？
Hehe, before, I probably wouldn't have cared much.
But now, if there will be cute uniforms, I really want to wear them.
You would be happy for that too, wouldn't you？ ...I guess.
I wonder if we can see them anytime soon. I really want to know more about them！
(...When she says something like that, even I feel a little embarrassed, too.)
I have new info about the new uniforms.
高嶺
Eh？ What is it？
The story itself was true, but now people from other clubs are asking, "Why just the tennis club？"
I see. Hah... That's too bad. Really...
By the way, I keep forgetting to tell you.
Hmm？ What？
▲高嶺＊＊▲, you are already very cute, you know？
...Hey, why do you say it all of a sudden！？ Such bad timing...！
I don't care anymore！
(Bad timing...？ Girls are really hard to understand...)
高嶺
Earlier, while I was shopping, I ran into a girl who I always competed with in tennis matches.
Huh？ Did you get a chance to talk with her？
Yeah, she called out to me. That girl is really good at tennis. I was totally beaten during my first match with her.
Eh！？ ▲高嶺＊＊▲, really？
I can laugh about it now, but it was really hard for me back then. Now, I still regret it.
Somehow, I think I can understand that feeling...
Hehe, we talked about the strategies our schools used for practice.
She told me some very useful techniques. I wonder if I should inform our captain.
Oh, are you becoming a spy now？
Don't exaggerate... Anyway, I'm not going to lose when it comes to information warfare. Hehehe...
(Don't tell me she's been holding a grudge ever since she lost to that girl.)
Later on, did you get any more information from your rival？
高嶺
Um, sort of...
Eh？ What's with that vagueness？
We talked about tennis, of course. ...But, we also talked about other things...
Other things？
Like... Our boyfriends...
Yeah, she also has a boyfriend, so we kind of shared the information...
U-Um... What kind of information？
That's... Well, a little bit of this, and a little bit of that... Um, something of that sort, okay？
(A little bit of this, and a little bit of that...？)
高嶺
By the way, people have been discussing tennis terminology lately.
Really？ What kind of terminology？
Well, like there are a lot of people who say "single" instead of "singles."
Ah, people who don't have an interest in tennis might say it wrong.
Yeah. Currently, there are a lot of people who just started playing tennis in high school, so they didn't learn the terms.
It's a bit weird that you have to add an "s" to the word "single," right？
And there are terms like "service" and "love" in English. Then there's also the term "mizutori" in Japanese.
Huh？ Is "mizutori" also a tennis term？
Eh？ That's what I thought. ...Maybe I'm wrong. I'd better research about this and I'll let you know.
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ really likes researching, huh？)
高嶺
We were discussing the term "mizutori," right？ It didn't originate from tennis though.
Huh？ Really？
The term we used in tennis is different from the one in religious ceremonies, but somehow it's related to Chinese feng shui.
You really did some research on this. Thanks for your effort.
Hehe, you're welcome.
It won't be fun if I have to remember all the terms...
Hehe. But if you know these terms, you'll have more fun when you play tennis, right？
Maybe not.
But aren't you curious about these terms？
Maybe.
Which one is your answer？ Hehe！
高嶺
Hey, can you go with me to the sports shop later？
Fine. What do you want to buy？
I'm thinking about buying a new pair of shoes. The current pair still works great, but they're getting worn out.
It's probably time for me to change my racket's strings too.
I see. Maybe I should change mine as well...
When was the last time you changed them？
...When was it？
For now, you should be changing them every three months...
...I've been using them much longer than that.
That's what I thought...
But you're amazing. Even with old strings, you can still play really well. I respect you. Really.
(She respects me for such a weird thing...)
高嶺
How is it？ Did you feel any differences after you changed the racket's strings？
The feeling is totally different, especially when I hit the ball.
Hehe, then that's good. It's a bit worrisome when you think about changing them, right？
▲高嶺＊＊▲, do you change them every 3 months？
I usually do that. But, it depends. Sometimes I change them when I feel like they need to be changed.
For me, by the time I think about changing them, I've already passed the recommended period.
Hehe, geez. If you want to win a tournament, you at least need to have standards, right？
I see. So, while we go to the same school, I'll change them at the same time as ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
...While we go to the same school？
Haha, sorry. I mean, even after we graduate, too.
Very well. Yeah. Hehe！
高嶺
By the way, there was an old man watching us practice. Did you notice？
Ah, I did. That guy kept smiling.
I wonder if he knows someone on our team. Maybe his granddaughter.
▲高嶺＊＊▲, I think he was there to watch you play.
Eh？ Really？ Hmm, but I can't recall ever meeting him before...
...Hehe.
Huh？
He was turning his head left and right when he looked at the ball. It was like a cat watching its toy.
Ah, when you say that, I can picture it.
Right？ But I didn't notice when he left though...
(So she doesn't know him？ I was wrong, huh？)
By the way, you were talking to that old man during practice. Did you know him？
高嶺
No. I thought he came to watch me play, but it was a misunderstanding.
Misunderstanding？
He has a granddaughter and she plays tennis as well. But when I asked him, it turned out that she was in another school.
Haha, that old man must be surprised then...
But, ▲高嶺＊＊▲, do you really look like his granddaughter？ What school does she go to？
...I forgot.
Eh？
I already forgot, so you can't go to see that girl. ...No, don't even think about seeing her. Got it？
(▲高嶺＊＊▲, I can tell what's on your mind...)
...What's your answer？
...Okay. I'm sorry.
Do you think my skill will improve if I practice with a backboard？
高嶺
Of course. If you don't see any improvement, that means you probably did it wrong.
Urgh.
Hehe. Currently, there are a lot of Japanese tennis players that become famous overseas.
Yeah, the youngest professional player ever is Japanese...
Yeah. I heard that when he was a child, he only practiced with a backboard.
Huh...？ Then it's probably quite an effective method.
I think so. You can check your form and evaluate your control while you're practicing.
But if you just practice recklessly, your form might even get worse, so you need to be careful.
...Practicing with a backboard isn't as easy as I thought.
Right, you can't take it too lightly.
(I should try harder during my next practice then.)
高嶺
How's your practice with a backboard going？
Hmm, it's pretty fun. Somehow, it's such a simple practice.
Hehe, you only need a backboard in order to practice, right？ Do you see any improvement？
I feel like my reflexes are getting faster.
Um, um, anything else？
And... Ah, right. I was wondering if you could take a look at my form and give me your opinion.
Um, fine. Maybe I should try practicing with a backboard with you, too.
Ah, that's nice. We'll have a date while practicing with a backboard.
Do you want to practice or go on a date？
Can I do both？
Hey, that's too greedy. Teeheehee！
高嶺
By the way, have you heard about the tournament trip？
Yeah, I've heard about it. I wonder if the venue is far from here.
Maybe we have to go by bus. ...It's very likely, right？
I guess so. Eh？ You don't like traveling by bus？
Um, I don't usually get carsick, but I'm not quite comfortable with sightseeing buses.
You can easily get sick in a sightseeing bus, huh？ Maybe you should take some medicine to prevent motion sickness in advance.
Eh？ You can't take motion sickness medicine？
No, that's not the case... But I'll get drowsy if I take the medicine. I'll just sleep through the whole trip.
Hah, what should I do？ Will I be allowed to go by train by myself？
(This is a tough situation. ...I don't know what I can do.)
By the way, we're only going to the nearby town for the tournament trip.
高嶺
Yeah, we'll go by train so I'm quite relieved now. But... I really have to be well prepared.
Right. And there might be a real trip sometime later.
Um... What do you think I should do？
I've done some research. Sitting near the front of the bus, not looking around too much, and wearing sunglasses help.
Really？
Yeah, avoid anything that'll stimulate your vision. You can try to look straight as if you were a bus driver too.
Look straight as if I were a bus driver？ Maybe I can practice doing that with arcade games first.
Ah, with car-racing games？ I wonder...
I should give it a try. Hey, will you accompany me there？
U-Um, okay.
All right. I'll try to win...！
(If she can overcome her motion sickness by playing games, it'll be such an amazing discovery...)
By the way, do members of the female tennis club quarrel sometimes？
高嶺
Well... There were two girls who used to be very good friends. They always practiced together.
But then they fell in love with the same guy and started to quarrel.
I see...
...If you were the guy they fell in love with, I would probably be like those girls.
Eh！？
Earlier, I couldn't understand why people would fight over something like that...
But now, I think I know how they feel when they think the guy they love might be snatched away.
I still want them to be friends again, but it might be quite difficult.
...For me to finally understand something like that, love sure is an amazing thing.
(Don't make that sad face...)
...Hey, what happened to the girls that were fighting？
高嶺
Oh, they reconciled.
So fast！ How？
They both confessed to him, and they both were rejected. They realized that neither of them could get him...
So, they finally decided to become friends again.
R-Really？ Girls' feelings are very mysterious...
Hehe. Now they are friends again. I'm glad my intuition was wrong this time.
Sorry. I said something weird earlier. I hope you'll just forget it.
...It's okay. Don't worry about it.
Thanks. Then let's go home.
(I don't want to see ▲高嶺＊＊▲ with that sad face again...)
Have you heard about our advisor, Suzuki-sensei？ His wife will give birth to a baby soon.
高嶺
Yeah！ He's been very fidgety lately. I finally understood why when I heard the news.
Hahaha. He really has been absent-minded lately.
Hehe. Right now, we have a plan to give him a surprise present.
Hmm？ That sounds fun.
Right？ Maybe the male members should join us too.
Then I'll ask the captain about this.
Okay, I'll leave it to you.
Wow, maybe Suzuki-sensei will be impressed and cry.
He is strict but he has his sensitive side. I can't wait to see how he will react.
By the way, Suzuki-sensei really cried, huh？
高嶺
Yeah, I even cried with him.
Some guys in our club cried too.
You're saying that, but what about you？
Huh？ What？
Hehe, okay. I'd better not ask.
But it'd be nice to have a husband like him... One day, we'll also...
Huh？
Nothing！ I was thinking that we gave him the present before practice, yet the practice was so hard.
Yeah, he reacted by being even more strict with us.
Hehe！ We can't lose to his happiness. Let's do our best.
Okay！
